# packages/schemas — shared contracts

One source of truth for the data contracts crossing web ↔ backend ↔ agent ↔ checkpointer. Both ends import from here; do not redefine these shapes anywhere else.

- Design from the artifact + boundary contracts enumerated in `docs/reference/feature-flow.md` Part C ("data contracts to be typed") and the schemas/ACI in `docs/reference/agent-architecture.md` Gate 5.
- Every artifact is Zod-validated at the backend boundary before it reaches state or the widget.
- Assist firewall: `correctIndex` / `explanation` / `hint` / `sourceQuote` never enter assist context.
